# Example VarMap Mapping File - Scope-Aware Format
# This file demonstrates the scope-aware mapping format.
# Each unique variable (by scope + name) appears only once.
#
# Format: FIRST LAST TYPE SCOPE CANONICAL NEW
# - FIRST: First occurrence (line:column)
# - LAST: Last occurrence (line:column) 
# - TYPE: func, param, or var
# - SCOPE: Scope where variable is defined
# - CANONICAL: Canonicalized name from VarMap
# - NEW: User-provided replacement name
#
# Example entries:
# FIRST LAST TYPE SCOPE CANONICAL NEW
1:10 1:10 func global fn_7823 addNumbers
1:12 1:25 param fn_add param_1 firstNumber
1:14 1:29 param fn_add param_2 secondNumber
1:21 1:35 var fn_add var_1 sum
2:5 2:10 var global var_1 globalData